30/09/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Belgrade is observing a day of mourning Wednesday (September 30th) in memory of a French citizen, attacked by Serbian hooligans, who died on Tuesday.
Brice Taton, 28, was beaten on September 17th in Belgrade before a match between Toulouse and Partizan Belgrade.
Police have arrested 11 people in connection with the attack, ten of whom are in custody.
President Boris Tadic, who is on a visit to Slovenia, expressed condolences to Taton's family Tuesday and promised that his assailants will be punished.
(Beta, RTS, B92, Tanjug, AP, Reuters - 29/09/09)
